Prepare
=======
Install conky:

    sudo apt-get install conky


Configuration
=============
Copy this folder to $HOME/.config , and link scripts/start_conky.sh to some place
executable, e.g. $HOME/bin .

    cp -r conky $HOME/.config/
    ln -s $HOME/.config/conky/scripts/start_conky.sh $HOME/bin/._start_conky.sh

Finally add a record to start Conky when boot finished. You can do this with
System -> Preferences -> Sessions .


